wikipedia_page.main: Walter Muir Kelly (15 April 1929 – 16 February 1993) was a Scottish footballer who played as a centre forward in the Football League for Bury, Doncaster Rovers, Stockport County and Chester, and for Raith Rovers in the Scottish Football League.His elder brother Willie Kelly was also a professional footballer; their father and two more brothers played at a lower level in Fife.

response: Walt or Walter Kelly may refer to:
*Raymond Walter Kelly (born 1941), American police commissioner in New York City a/k/a Ray Kelly
